Durban - A driver transporting school children was killed in an accident on the N2 near Murchison on Tuesday morning. According to Netcare 911's Shawn Herbst reports from the scene indicated that a minibus taxi transporting school children of various ages and a heavy motor vehicle were involved in a collision. "Paramedics assessed the scene and found that the taxi driver had sustained fatal injuries and was declared deceased on the scene." Herbst said the other fourteen patients sustained injuries ranging from moderate to serious. He said some of the victims required Advanced Life Support intervention. "Once stabilised all the patients were transported by various ambulance services to hospital for further treatment." He added that all the necessary authorities were on scene. Earlier today a man sustained serious injuries after the back wheel of a minibus taxi had broken off while travelling downhill and crashed through the window of a light delivery vehicle which was parked at a robot. The incident took place in Redhill, Durban. POST